  30:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****     [..]
  31:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****       Alternatively to the normal programming mode, a DMA channel can be programmed by a list of tr
  32:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****       linked-list (list of Node items). Each node is defined by its data structure.
  33:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****       Each node specifies a standalone DMA channel.
  34:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****       When enabled, the DMA channel fetch the first linked-list node from SRAM (known as head node)
  35:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****       next linked list node will be fetched and executed. This operation is repeated until the end 
  36:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****       linked-list queue. Optionally, the linked-list can be linear where the last linked-list queue
  37:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****       to another queue node or circular where the last linked-list node is linked to any linked-lis
  38:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c **** 
  39:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****           (+) Linear linked-list:
  40:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****               The DMA channel fetch and execute all DMA linked-list queue from first node (head nod
  41:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****               (tail node) ones. When the last node is completed, the DMA channel remains in idle st
  42:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****               transfer can be lunched.
  43:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c **** 
  44:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****           (+) Circular linked-list:
  45:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****               The DMA channel fetch and execute all DMA linked-list queue from first node (head nod
  46:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****               node). When last node is executed, the DMA channel fetches the first circular node an
  47:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****               the same sequence in an infinite loop (Circular transfer). To stop the DMA channel, a
  48:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****               required. This linked-list mode replaces the legacy circular transfers.
  49:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c **** 
  50:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****     [..]
  51:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****       In order to reduce linked-list queue executing time and power consumption, the DMA channel su
  52:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****       dynamic linked-list format. In fact, the DMA supports the execution of 2 types of linked-list
  53:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****       dynamic.
  54:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c **** 
  55:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****           (+) Static linked-list:
  56:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****               The static linked-list format refers to the full linked-list node where all DMA chann
  57:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****               fetched and executed independently of the redundancy of information.
  58:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c **** 
  59:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****           (+) Dynamic linked-list:
  60:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****               The dynamic linked-list format refer to the customized linked-list node where only DM
  61:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****               parameters are fetched and executed (Example: data size = 20 on previous node, and da
  62:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****               current node => No need to update it).
  63:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c **** 
  64:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****       For linked-list transfers, the DMA channel can execute the linked-list queue node by node. Th
  65:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****       link step mode. When activated, enabling the DMA channel first time allows to fetch the head 
  66:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****       then it stops. Then, another DMA channel enable is needed to execute the node. After that, ke
  67:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****       DMA channel is needed to execute each node until the end of linked-list queue. When the linke
  68:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****       circular, enabling the DMA channel in an infinite loop is required to keep the DMA channel ru
  69:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****       is useful for debug purpose or asynchronously executing queue nodes.
  70:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c **** 
  71:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****     [..]
  72:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****       Each DMA channel transfer (normal or linked-list), is highly configurable according to DMA ch
  73:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****       integrated in devices. These configuration can be :
  74:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c **** 
  75:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****           (+) Repeated block configuration :
  76:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****               If the feature is supported, the DMA channel can performs a repeated block transfers.
  77:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****               dimension addressing transfers, this feature can transfer n iteration of programmed b
  78:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****               transfer is the legacy data size). Additional to the repeat count of a block, DMA cha
  79:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****               jump after at burst and block level. The jump length is a programmable parameter defi
  80:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****                (++) Jump at burst level :
  81:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****                     The DMA channel keep an empty area, between each 2 consecutive bursts transmitt
  82:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****                (++) Jump at block level :
