  86:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****               The DMA channel transfers can be conditioned by hardware signals edges (rising or fal
  87:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****               triggers. Trigger condition can be applied at :
  88:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****                (++) Single/Burst level :
  89:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****                     Each single/burst data transmission is conditioned by a signal trigger hit.
  90:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****                (++) Block level :
  91:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****                     Each block data transmission is conditioned by a signal trigger hit.
  92:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****                (++) Repeated block level :
  93:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****                     Each repeated block data transmission is conditioned by a signal trigger hit.
  94:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****                (++) Node level :
  95:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****                     Each node execution is conditioned by a signal trigger hit.
  96:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dma_ex.c ****               The DMA channel can report a trigger overrun when detects more than 2 trigger signal 
